<!DOCTYPE html>
<html>
    <head>

    </head>
    <body>
        <h1>{{ title }}</h1>
        <p>{{ description }}</p>
        <code>drush {{ title }}</code>
        <h2>Aliases:</h2>
            <ul>
            {% for alias in aliases %}
                <li>{{ alias }}</li>
            {% endfor %}
            </ul>
        <h2>Arguments:</h2>
        {% for argument in arguments %}
            <code>{{ argument }}</code>
        {% endfor %}
        <h2>Options:</h2>
        <code>--description : Describe the archive contents.</code>
        <code>--generator : The generator name to store in the MANIFEST file. The default is "Drush archive-dump".</code>
        <h2>Examples:</h2>
        <p>Write an archive containing 3 sites in it.</p>
        <code>drush drush archive-dump default,example.com,foo.com</code>
        <p>Save archive containing all sites in a multi-site.</p>
        <code>drush drush archive-dump @sites</code>
        <p>Save archive to custom location.</p>
        <code>drush drush archive-dump default --destination=/backups/mysite.tar</code>
        <p>Omits any .git directories found in the tree as well as sites/default/files.</p>
        <code>drush drush archive-dump --tar-options="--exclude=.git --exclude=sites/default/files"</code>
        <p>Placeholder %files is replaced with the real path for the current site, and that path is excluded.</p>
        <code>drush drush archive-dump --tar-options="--exclude=%files"</code>
    </body>
</html>
